description:
In this episode, we learn about the past, present and future of the Seventh Day Adventist Church. The Reformation began as a long process of rediscovering the truth that had been lost in the dark ages. The rediscovery was progressive and as the reformation drew to a close in Europe in the late 1700s, the epicentre of Christian innovation and progress would shift to America in the 1800s. In the mid 1800s, the Seventh Day Adventist Church would rise as a movement to call people back to the Bible and take the message of God around the world.

To find out more information about the Seventh-Day Adventist Church visit our website to read our extended article.
